icher Gewalt und Individuum - und damit in die conditio humana - erlaubt.  aFrom electrotherapy to the electric chair and to »electro shock therapy« (EST): This volume analyzes dispositifs of electro-medical violence and culminates in an analysis of life on the New York State EST ward.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aAmerika. 4aAmerikanische Geschichte. 4aElektrischer Stuhl. 4aElektroschocktherapie. 4aGeschichtswissenschaft. 4aGewalt. 4aMedizin. 4aMedizingeschichte. 4aNew York. 4aUSA. 4aWissenschaft. 4aWissenschaftsgeschichte. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aAmerican History.  aElectric Chair.  aElectroconvulsive Therapy.  aHistory of Medicine.  aHistory of Science.  aHistory.  aMedicine.  aNew York.  aScience.  aUsa.  aViolence.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783110401226oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839428023zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839428023423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839428023/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-TGPb2014  aZDB-23-TGPc2014d2016